sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Client
    participant Co as Coordinator<br/>(any node)
    participant R1 as Replica 1
    participant R2 as Replica 2
    participant R3 as Replica 3

    Note over C,R3: Write flow (W=2, N=3)
    C->>Co: PUT key, value
    Co->>Co: hash(key) -> ring lookup
    par fan-out to replicas
        Co->>R1: write (value, vclock)
        Co->>R2: write (value, vclock)
        Co->>R3: write (value, vclock)
    end
    R1-->>Co: ack
    R2-->>Co: ack
    Co-->>C: success (W=2 met)
    R3-->>Co: ack (async)
    alt R3 down
        Note over Co,R3: hinted handoff stored<br/>on neighbor; replays on revive
    end

    Note over C,R3: Read flow (R=2, N=3)
    C->>Co: GET key
    par query replicas
        Co->>R1: read
        Co->>R2: read
        Co->>R3: read
    end
    R1-->>Co: value, vclock_a
    R2-->>Co: value, vclock_b
    Co->>Co: compare vector clocks (R=2 met)
    alt versions agree
        Co-->>C: value
    else conflict (concurrent vclocks)
        Co-->>C: all conflicting versions
        Note over Co,R3: read repair pushes<br/>newest to stale replica
    end
